---

<section id="booking" class="relative bg-estate-black-soft py-24 md:py-32 lg:py-40 border-t border-chalk-white/10">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1400px] px-5 md:px-10 lg:px-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[5fr_7fr] gap-12 lg:gap-16">
    <div>
      <h2 data-split-reveal class="text-display-section text-balance-display">
        Tell Us About Your Dog.
      </h2>
      <p data-reveal class="mt-6 max-w-[44ch] text-base md:text-lg text-stone-light leading-relaxed">
        Every relationship starts with a free home consultation. Before we meet, it helps to
        know the basics: your dog's name, breed, and age, their usual walking routine, and
        anything that makes them anxious, reactive, or excitable around other dogs. If they're
        on medication or have specific feeding instructions, mention that too. Fill in what you
        can and we'll cover the rest when we visit.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div data-reveal class="trigger-panel">
      <p class="trigger-panel__eyebrow text-sm text-stone">What we'll ask for</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 divide-y divide-chalk-white/10 border-t border-b border-chalk-white/10">
        <li class="py-4 text-stone-light">Your name and best contact number</li>
        <li class="py-4 text-stone-light">Your dog's breed and age</li>
        <li class="py-4 text-stone-light">Their usual routine and any quirks</li>
      </ul>

      <button type="button" class="js-open-booking cta-button group mt-8">
        <span class="cta-button__fill"></span>
        <span class="relative z-10 flex items-center justify-between gap-6">
          Book a Consultation
          <span class="cta-button__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&#8594;</span>
        </span>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
